pageContext.description: Cutting edge sharp, and sharply recurved at each end. Blade slightly concave on both face, and uniformly thick and it tapers sharply towards the cutting edge. Short side-flanges with the edges hammered over towards each other. Butt is rough and thick, and has been broken off in ancient times. On one edge of the blade are two parallel regular indentations, running from one side to the other.
pageContext.surface: Fairly smooth thin dark brown patina; bronze colour along cutting-edge, at the top of the taper, and on the tops of the flanges. Dots of [ad?] on the outer side of one flange.
pageContext.toSearch: Castle Meadows, Snape, Bedale, North Yorkshire Dl8 2tt, UK
